  "model": "gpt-4o-mini",
  "response_text": "Creating a healthy meal plan for someone with limited time and shared kitchen space requires simplicity, versatility, and minimal cooking. Here’s a one-week meal plan that emphasizes easy-to-make meals, batch cooking, and healthy ingredients. Feel free to adjust portion sizes and ingredients based on personal preferences or dietary needs.\n\n### Meal Plan Overview\n\n**Key Ingredients:**\n- Whole grains (brown rice, quinoa, oats)\n- Canned beans (black beans, chickpeas)\n- Fresh vegetables (spinach, bell peppers, carrots, tomatoes)\n- Frozen vegetables (broccoli, mixed veggies)\n- Eggs\n- Lean proteins (chicken breast, tofu)\n- Nuts and seeds (almonds, chia seeds)\n- Greek yogurt\n- Fruits (bananas, apples, berries)\n\n### Daily Meal Breakdown\n\n#### Day 1\n- **Breakfast:** Overnight oats with Greek yogurt, chia seeds, and berries.\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa salad with black beans, corn, diced bell peppers, and lime dressing.\n- **Dinner:** Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables and brown rice.\n\n#### Day 2\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie with spinach, banana, Greek yogurt, and a spoonful of peanut butter.\n- **Lunch:** Hummus and veggie wrap with whole grain tortilla, spinach, and assorted veggies.\n- **Dinner:** Baked chicken breast with roasted sweet potatoes and steamed broccoli.\n\n#### Day 3\n- **Breakfast:** Greek yogurt with sliced banana and a sprinkle of nuts.\n- **Lunch:** Chickpea salad with diced cucumber, tomatoes, and a lemon vinaigrette.\n- **Dinner:** Vegetable stir-fry with brown rice and scrambled eggs.\n\n#### Day 4\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal topped with sliced apples and cinnamon.\n- **Lunch:** Leftover chicken from Day 2 in a salad with mixed greens and vinaigrette.\n- **Dinner:** Tofu tacos with black beans, salsa, and avocado.\n\n#### Day 5\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie bowl topped with granola and fresh fruit.\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa and vegetable bowl with a tahini dressing.\n- **Dinner:** Stuffed bell peppers with quinoa, black beans, and spices.\n\n#### Day 6\n- **Breakfast:** Greek yogurt parfait with mixed berries and a handful of granola.\n- **Lunch:** Veggie and bean soup (make a large batch to last for a few days).\n- **Dinner:** Zucchini noodles (or whole grain pasta) with marinara sauce and sautéed spinach.\n\n#### Day 7\n- **Breakfast:** Whole grain toast with avocado and poached egg.\n- **Lunch:** Leftover veggie soup with added greens for extra nutrition.\n- **Dinner:** Grilled chicken or tofu with a side of quinoa and steamed frozen vegetables.\n\n### Tips for Meal Prep and Cooking in a Shared Kitchen\n1. **Batch Cooking:** Cook grains (quinoa, rice) and proteins (chicken, tofu) in bulk at the beginning of the week and store them in the fridge for easy access.\n2. **Utilize Freezer:** Keep frozen vegetables on hand for quick stir-fries and soups.\n3. **One-Pan Meals:** Opt for recipes that can be made in one pot or pan to minimize cleanup.\n4. **Simple Snacks:** Keep healthy snacks like nuts, fruits, and yogurt available for quick grabs between meals.\n5. **Share Ingredients:** Coordinate with roommates to share common ingredients like spices and condiments to save space and reduce costs.\n\nWith this plan, you can eat healthily while managing limited time and shared kitchen space efficiently. Enjoy!",
